eNCA's Barry Bateman reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The e-Commerce and small businesses sector could be the biggest losers if the Post Office and Icasa have their way. The state parties are going to court to enforce their interpretation of the Postal Services. READ: SA Post Office cash-strapped If they win, the Post Office would have the exclusive mandate to deliver parcels weighing less than a kilogram. But some question if the Post Office is really up to the task. WATCH: SA Post Office in crisis | Post Office said to be commercially insolvent The organisation suffered an operating loss of R3-billion in the last financial year and it's expected to incur a further R2-billion loss in the next year. * eNCA’s Barry Bateman reports.